I wanted to rate this because people are saying it might not taste like New York Style pizza. My grandparents had a place in Syosset, Long Island and they loved to take us to Mario's Pizza. The pizza here tastes like Mario's. So I would say it is New York Style and tastes really good. The only problem is it is expensive because it's on State. People are saying $5 for a slice is cheap, it really isn't when you are talking about a regular cheese pizza slice. Regardless, I enjoyed eating pizza here.</text>

<Review>I recently ran over a nail in almost brand new large truck tires, luckily it was not through the sidewall. I decided to call Valley Tire & Tackle in Fort Jones to see if they had time and the ability to repair my tire. They said it would be super quick and that yes they could fix it for around $10+ dollars.

So I went in around 45 minutes later. They quickly took the truck back into the shop and went about removing the tire and getting to work. After about 15 minutes they were done. They brought my truck back out front and told me no charge - on the house this time. So I gave the worker who helped a few dollars as a tip.

Overall, my first experience with them was fantastic. Customer service was outstanding, price (if I paid) was more than reasonable, and its local which I love to support where possible. I recommend giving these guys a call first before heading up to Medford or Yreka - give them a chance to earn your business. I will be returning.</Review>< Pictures>

<Text>This is a fantastic small tennis shop. Pricing on tennis accessories like grips and backpacks are pretty much in line with the cheapest online pricing. Selection can be a little light but they have a lot of the more popular products.

The service is fantastic. It's the best pricing I've found on good string jobs in the area. They're also very well stocked on different strings. Hyper G is around $24. They might take a day or two to get your rackets back but seem to be willing to work with you.

Joey was extremely considerate. I came by again when my racket string got damaged and he was very helpful then too. The prices here are also quite competitive, and I got a brand new racket as well! So come take a look for yourself and see what this place has to offer.< /Review><Pics>None< /Pics>< Resp>

<Time>1576472275715< /Time><rating>1</rating>< Text>
Huge disappointment. We had a party of 15 going to the restaurant with a reservation. We didn't get a waiter until around 15 minutes for some reason. We ordered our drinks and appetizers and that came out. However, they didn't provide us with utensils or plates until after asking 3 times. We then ordered our meals after waiting another 15 minutes for a waiter to take our orders.  We ordered 5 Steak and Potatoes only for the waiter to tell us that they had 1 normal steak left and that they would have to use porterhouse steaks instead. One of us tried to get the steaks at the same price, but we couldn't get it at the normal steak price so 4 of us had to change our orders. The food came out at a comfortable pace, but there weren't any potatoes for the steak and potatoes, which the waiter didn't notify us about. Another complaint was that a person ordered pork chops, but it was pink when it should have been completely cooked. The restaurant took that off the bill. Overall, the experience was not great and the service was satisfactory.
TLDR: Slow service, no normal steaks and no potatoes for the steak and potatoes, and  a pork chop that was not fully cooked.</Text>

I reserved a table for 13 people 2 weeks in advance of dining date & stated we were celebrating a birthday. < text>
I love Macaroni Grill. The service is always consistently good, and so is the food. There's never too long of a wait to get your food. It all tastes fresh too. I would recommend making reservations when you go here though. I order the Shrimp Portofino, and it is excellent. If you're a fan of fish you should get the sole. I had a couple gift cards. <userid>115334614907471527077</userid>< name>
Clayton Stratton</name>
<Date>1567563695877<//Date>< rating>
2<//rating>
< Text>
This review is for a Grubhub delivery.

The food was good and packaged well aside from the oil and vinegar cups for the bread having opened and spilled inside the bag.

I ordered the signature truffle Mac and cheese and crispy mozzarella bites. The crispy mozz bites seemed like they had been way overcooked as they were all hemorrhaging dry, fried mozzarella and the insides were hollow.

My biggest problem however was ordering pasta from a restaurant whose menu consists primarily of pasta dishes, and not getting ANY silverware or napkins. How was this missed?? I had to call down to the front desk of my hotel and have someone bring a fork because no one at Romano's threw one in, and the Grubhub drivers don't stick around long enough to verify an order with the customer.

I disagree with the fundamental trend of sacrificing service for convenience and with a Grubhub delivery, I'm noticing no one takes accountability for an order. Sure, I can call the restaurant, but do I want to wait another 30 minutes for someone to drive back out to make my order right? This is compounded by the fact that my tip is pre-emptively applied so my one method of rewarding good service or highlighting bad is taken away from me.

I think both the restaurant and GH could do better. The restaurant needs to take better care with remote orders and ensure they are all 100% before going out the door, since problem resolution is much more complicated and time consuming; and I think GH as a service provider needs to emphasize *correct* service over *fast* service and incentivize workers at all points in the chain to follow suit.

I'm upset at RMG for not knowing their business and failing to include silverware to a hotel order for a food that *cannot* be eaten with hands, and GH needs to ensure orders that go through their process are correct before eating a customer's time and money. Next time I need to eat, I'll just go sit down at the restaurant. At least then when there's a problem, I can settle it immediately.< /Text>

< Text>
Party of six celebrating a birthday.
Service was attentive.
Large white sheets of paper covered the tables,  crayons provided for the young at heart.
For a Wednesday night, it was not crowded at dinner time, approximately 6 p.m.
3 of us had the chicken marsala. 1 had spaghetti and meatballs, shrimp scampi, and another had pasta alfredo.
The food was good, but not great in my humble opinion.
My chicken marsala was good but lacked the depth the marsala sauce typically carries.
The others in our party did seem pleased with their dish though.
Warm bread was served along with dipping sauce of spices and herbs in olive oil and balsamic vinegar may also be added.
It was very good.
The ladies room could be a bit more clean, and parking lot had a lot more cars than patrons.
We thought the place was packed judging by the cars in the lot near the entrance into the restaurant,  but only a couple of seated patrons.
Choice of chocolate cake or baked cheesecake with sliced strawberries on the side for the birthday girl.
I will most likely return to try another dish sometime in the future.</Text>

<Review>When my wife and I were first married, we used to save so we could go to one of our favorite places-Romano's Macaroni Grill! Then we moved away from any locations and have missed it.  Traveling through the area today, we were excited to see a RMG! We saw the reviews, but thought that surely they must be mistaken, this is Romano's after all...right?  Here's our experience.  The greeter was very friendly and courteous to us throughout the visit.  He greeted us warmly when we entered, came and chatted briefly with us while we were waiting for our food, and opened the door for us when we left.  The server was alright as well.  But, that's where the positives ended.  Granted, I am comparing things with a memory, but if this is indicative of current practices, things have definitely changed.  The oil and basalmic poured out with the appetizer bread that used to be served have been replaced by some oil and pepper.  The small loaf was cold and hard.  My shoes stuck to the floor around our table.  The restroom was dirty and in need of repair.  Gone was the music piped into the restaurant and the atmosphere that was created there in the past.  When the food arrived, I thought the chicken I ate was off for some reason.  After a couple of bites I realized what it was.  It tasted exactly like the chicken that is reconstituted after being frozen in a microwave dinner.  I didn't eat any more of it.  The pasta was well cooked, but the sauces were lacking.  To cap it off, a family member who has the chicken parmesan came home with a very upset stomach.  I still don't want to give up on RMG, with so many GOOD memories from the past.  But I'm left with the impression that I should leave my experiences with RMG at that, the good memories.  Disappointing to say the least.< /Review><user_name>Ron Dillender<//user_name>< resp>

< Review>
Very crowded the night we went but the food was fabulous and our waiter went above and beyond the expected to make our dinner with my in-laws a lovely experience.   There was a slightly more quiet dining area in the bar area that would have been my preference, when available. The open kitchen was interesting to see, although a little noisy, but part of the experience. They dealt nicely with food allergies and during our order easily allowed us to switch out the offending food for a safe alternative. I usually eat half my dinners and take half home but the specialty pasta dish was so good, I missed having leftovers. The brussel sprouts were a game changer for holiday dinners. Seriously good food. My in-laws liked the wine offered and ended up buying the whole bottle to take home.<//Review>

< Text>
The food was very good, and the portions extremely generous; you'll definitely have leftovers, which makes the slightly high prices worth it. The waitstaff was pleasant and the service was fast - we got our salads about five minutes after we placed our orders, and the entr√©es arrived before I had even finished my salad. This place also serves fresh baked bread (focaccia) for the table, which was nice and hot. I ordered the classic truffle mac and cheese, which was a little bit spicy (comes with black pepper in it) and very cheesy, but a little drier than I was hoping it would be (I like my mac and cheese very creamy). Overall, this is a nice place that I would visit a few times a year because of the prices and how heavy the food is.</Text>

< Review>
EDIT (Jun/2018): This place is decaying fast. It appears their corporate overlords decided that they only want your money and don't care for your experience. On our last visit, we had to wait 40+ minutes to sit, even though the place was about 1/4 full. Empty tables everywhere and no servers to take customers. To me, this indicates a company that wants to keep costs low by employing fewer server than they need. After our wait, we were served by a very disinterested waiter. The free bread (one of the selling points of the place) is still there, but was clearly not fresh as it used to be. They now charge extra for salads and soup. In the end, we spent around 3h+ to have a very dissatisfying experience. I won't be coming back anytime soon. It's a real shame, since the place used to be a good place to eat casually.

OLD REVIEW:
Good "bang for the buck". It's not "authentic" Italian food, but the taste is good. Not super expensive and the setting is very nice for what you pay for. A nice loaf of bread is included as an appetizer when you order any entree.< /Review>

< Review>
I'm NEVER one to complain, but my experience here on 10/7/18 warrants it!!

It was an absolute disaster from the beginning. When we got first got there, we were told that there was approx. 25 min wait for a party of 4... no big thing...

After my personal observation, I noticed that there were several open tables where the recent parties just departed. These tables sat open for 15 mins or more, and then I realized that who ever did the scheduling did not have enough bussers available. I only saw a bus boy cleaning tables.  TALK ABOUT BEING GROSSLY UNDERSTAFFED! C'MON MAN!

After inquiring with the host/manager after 35 mins, we were then seated. The table wasnt prepared, no utensil settings, no glasses... really?!? Being patient, I let it slide...

Waiter eventually came around and took our order after sitting arnd for 10 mins. Again, no utensil settings but we got our drinks... and bread...  but no utensils. I finally had to ask another waiter if we could get some settings...

We placed 3 orders of appetizers; calamari, mac n cheese bites, and fresh mozzarella. Calamari came w/in 10 mins of the initial order. We proceeded to order our main dishes.

Our main dish came in 35 mins w/in ordering it, but the other appetizers havent arrived yet and no explanation... wth?!  After working into our main dish, the remaining appetizers came 42 mins since placing it and 7 mins AFTER the main dish arrived.

After waiting all that time, we really didnt have any appetite to eat any more... would you or any one??? C'MON MAN!

Where is John Taffer when you need him? Good grief, talk about a bootleg operation! C'MON MAN!

If you have time to burn and really dont care about the quality of service, then this is your place. Sadly, for the price that they demand, you're better off cooking the meal yourself without the unwanted stress!!

In my personal observation, this place lacks:
* communication
* integrity
* compassion
* desire

Sadly, we were among 5 other parties who were waiting for service in this bootleg operation. John Taffer would scream out, "you're in the customer service business and your livelihood depends on it!! Are you f$&n crazy?!?"

Needless to say, our party left extremely disappointed. If I was a representative from this corporation and experienced what I went through, there would be a lot of unemployed people with the fear of this place shutting down..

This place is broken and needs help! Sorry to be brutally honest, but I'm pulling for you guys to stay in business...<//Review>
